doc.after: Order Charadriiformes Family Scolopacidae Scolopacidae is a large and diverse family of small to medium sized shorebirds which includes the sandpipers curlews godwits shanks tattlers woodcocks snipes dowitchers and phalaropes Most eat small invertebrates picked out of the mud or sand Different lengths of legs and bills enable multiple species to feed in the same habitat particularly on the coast without direct competition for food
